3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses a bipartite graph to map the Hamiltonian cycle problem, which is a technique commonly used in computational geometry. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The Hamiltonian cycle problem is also relevant in game theory, as it is used to model the traveling salesman problem. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the time complexity of determining the existence of a Hamiltonian cycle, which is a topic within computational complexity theory.
